@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

 URLLink is a set of AmigaDOS batch files that allow you to create a link to a
 web site, ftp site , an email address or any other kind of URL address. A link
 consists of a dynamically created batch file and an icon assigned to it. When
 you click on that icon, your standard web browser or mail client will be started
 with the provided address. To demonstrate what can be done with this I included
 an example that adds additional entries to the context menus of IBrowse which
 create a link on your Opus Magellan Desktop.

@endnode

