@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

 CreateURLLink:

 · AmigaOS/68K >= Release 2.0 (Version 36)

   Should run under AROS/68K and MorphOS/PPC as well. Couldn't test this.

 · OpenURL, can be downloaded at Aminet:@{"comm/www/OpenURL30.lha" rxs "IF ~SHOW('L','openurl.library') THEN CALL ADDLIB('openurl.library',3,-66);url='http://ftp.uni-paderborn.de/pub/aminet/comm/www/OpenURL30.lha';OpenURL(url,SHOW,TOFRONT,NEWWIN,LAUNCH);EXIT" }


 CreateLinkOnDesktop additionally needs:

 · AmigaOS/68K >= Release 3.0 (Version 39)

 · MUI >= Release 3.8

 · BetterString.mcc/.mcp Version >= 11.3

 · MUIRequestString, can be downloaded at Aminet:@{"util/batch/MUIRequestStr.lha" rxs "IF ~SHOW('L','openurl.library') THEN CALL ADDLIB('openurl.library',3,-66);url='http://ftp.uni-paderborn.de/pub/aminet/util/batch/MUIRequestStr.lha';OpenURL(url,SHOW,TOFRONT,NEWWIN,LAUNCH);EXIT" }

 · SubStr , can be downloaded at Aminet:@{"util/cli/SubStr.lha" rxs "IF ~SHOW('L','openurl.library') THEN CALL ADDLIB('openurl.library',3,-66);url='http://ftp.uni-paderborn.de/pub/aminet/util/cli/SubStr.lha';OpenURL(url,SHOW,TOFRONT,NEWWIN,LAUNCH);EXIT" }

 · IBrowse 2.x

 · Opus Magellan 5.xx

@endnode

@node INSTALLATION "Installation"

 Automatically

  Use the provided installation scripts.


 Manually

  Copy Icons/#? to ENVARC:sys/

  Rename S/CreateLinkOnDesktop.<your_language> to S/CreateLinkOnDesktop

  Copy S/CreateLinkOnDesktop to S:

  Copy S/CreateURLLink to S:

  Ensure that all files copied to S: have there protection bits set to RWEDS.

  Copy URLLink.guide to HELP:English/


 If you want to call CreateLinkOnDesktop from IBrowse read @{"this" link CONFIGURATION}

@endnode

@node USAGE "Usage"

 Call from the shell as following:

 CreateURLLink:

  @{i}CreateURLLink URL/A,LINKNAME/A,PATH/A@{ui}

 All arguments are required.

  URL       is the full URL of the address the link should point to, e.g.

            @{fg shine}
            http://www.holzammer.net
            file:///Work:Introduction.pdf
            ftp://cz.aminet.net/pub/aminet/
            mailto:Development@Holzammer.net
            "mailto:Development@Holzammer.net?subject=Bug Report"
            @{fg text}

            If the URL contains spaces the @{i}whole@{ui} URL must be enclosed by "".


  LINKNAME  is the name of the link, e.g.
            @{fg shine}
            "Homepage of URLLink"
            Introduction
            "Czech Aminet (Full Mirror)"
            "Send a mail to the autor of URLLink"
            "Send a bug report to the author of URLLink"
            @{fg text}

            If the linkname includes spaces you need to enclose it with "".
            You may not use longer descriptions than the longest possible
            length of filenames the filesystem supports - 5.
            So for FastFileSystem the limit is usually 30-5=25,
            for SmartFileSystem the limit is 107-5=98.


  PATH      is the path the created link file should be saved at.
            If the path contains spaces it must be enclosed by "".
            It @{b}must@{ub} end in @{b}:@{ub} or @{b}/@{ub} !!

            Work:Docs/ is a vaild path,
            Work:Docs is NOT !


  ?         Shows above template and asks you for input.



 CreateLinkOnDesktop:

  @{i}CreateLinkOnDesktop URL/A@{ui}

 The argument is required.

  URL       is the full URL of the address the link should point to, e.g.

            @{fg shine}
            http://www.holzammer.net
            file:///Work:Introduction.pdf
            ftp://cz.aminet.net/pub/aminet/
            mailto:Development@Holzammer.net
            "mailto:Development@Holzammer.net?subject=Bug Report"
            @{fg text}

            If the URL contains spaces the @{i}whole@{ui} URL must be enclosed by "".

  A requester will pop up to ask you for the LINKNAME. There is no shell argument
  for this as it is not really intended to call from shell directly but to call
  from IBrowse's context menu.

@endnode

@node CONFIGURATION "Configuration"

  This chapter will explain how to configure IBrowse to add some items to
  its context menus that will create a link on your (Opus Magellan) Desktop.
  There is no way to do this automatically, so you have to do it yourself.

  Ok, step by step:

  Read the chapters about @{"Requirements" link REQUIREMENTS} and @{"Installation" link INSTALLATION}.

  Start IBrowse 2.x and open its settings window.

  Jump to GUI/FAB Menus.

  There are three groups arranged horizontally.
  In the middle one you find th possible actions.
  The right one contains the structure of the context menus.

  Open node "Link" and drag/drop action "Custom" below it, directly to the position
  you'd like it to be.

  Now click onto the new item and input a description into the first string gadget,
  e.g. @{i}Create a link on Desktop@{ui}

  Choose @{i}Command@{ui} from the cycle menu.
  In the string gagdet besides input S:CreateLinkOnDesktop.
  The string gadget on the right should be set to @{i}%l@{ui}.

  Now open the Page menu and repeat what you have done for the Link menu.

  Now save the configuration, load a document and test the new entries of
  the link and Page context menus.


@endnode

